    "created_at": "2015-12-28T15:20:23Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-12-28T15:41:00Z",
    "body": "Here are more information on notifications in Win 10 for desktop apps (and how to make them persist): http://blogs.msdn.com/b/tiles_and_toasts/archive/2015/10/15/quickstart-handling-toast-activations-from-win32-apps-in-windows-10.aspx\n\nQuote: \"So instead of requiring Win32 apps to use an event handler for activation (IToastNotification::add_Activated) that only works while the app is running, we now allow Win32 apps to use a COM server that can be invoked when users interact with the toast at any time.\"\n"
